{"TopicId":216724,"ForumId":121,"TopicTitle":"TWR of exactly 1.0 for the entire trip to the moon and back.","CreatedByName":"Cashdesigner","CreatedById":228717,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T18:29:23Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Cashdesigner","CreatedById":228717,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T18:29:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDitto\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Scarecrow71","CreatedById":210112,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-19T22:52:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.0 might - and that\u0027s a pretty strong MIGHT - get you off the launchpad.\u00A0 Maybe.\u00A0 And just barely.\u00A0 And will waste a whole lot of fuel to do so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe biggest detriment to this challenge, apart from having zero rules other than \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E to the Mun and back, is that the stock game doesn\u0027t display \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E in any fashion.\u00A0 You need a mod like Micro-Engineer to display this for you.\u00A0 Not to mention that you will be fiddling with the throttle the entire time you are flying (and there may be times where your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E is less than 1.0 due to low gravity and the engine you are using).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll told, I\u0027m not sure this challenge is do-able.\u00A0 I mean, I\u0027ll give it a shot at some point...but I don\u0027t think you can get off the launchpad at 1.0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"s_gamer101","CreatedById":205435,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-22T16:44:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of exactly 1 doesn\u0027t get you anywhere because having a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1 means that the weight and the trust of your ship ar equal and therefore cancel each other out. This challenge is physically impossible\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"s_gamer101","CreatedById":205435,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-23T11:01:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681944774\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/20/2023 at 12:52 AM, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand there may be times where your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is less than 1.0 due to low gravity and the engine you are using\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLower gravity means higher \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E, not lower \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-23T12:48:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224276137\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221682247662\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022205435\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022s_gamer101\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, s_gamer101 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLower gravity means higher \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E, not lower \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat assumes the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E means \u0022\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E=1 at Kerbin\u0027s Surface\u0022 and not \u0022\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E=1 relative to the gravity field you\u0027re in right now, changing throughout the challenge.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow both are fine assumptions, but there\u0027s no way to know if the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E meant one or the other.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMostly because the entire challenge is:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274593\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681928964\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228717\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cashdesigner\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/19/2023 at 2:29 PM, Cashdesigner said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDitto\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-23T20:50:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a revision of \u0022a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.01 to the Mun and Back\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerkyJerkyWreaksHavoc","CreatedById":207646,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-23T22:39:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224274688\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221681944774\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210112\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Scarecrow71\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/19/2023 at 6:52 PM, Scarecrow71 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.0 might - and that\u0027s a pretty strong MIGHT - get you off the launchpad.\u00A0 Maybe.\u00A0 And just barely.\u00A0 And will waste a whole lot of fuel to do so.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe biggest detriment to this challenge, apart from having zero rules other than \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E to the Mun and back, is that the stock game doesn\u0027t display \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in any fashion.\u00A0 You need a mod like Micro-Engineer to display this for you.\u00A0 Not to mention that you will be fiddling with the throttle the entire time you are flying (and there may be times where your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is less than 1.0 due to low gravity and the engine you are using).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAll told, I\u0027m not sure this challenge is do-able.\u00A0 I mean, I\u0027ll give it a shot at some point...but I don\u0027t think you can get off the launchpad at 1.0.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell Actually\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:blink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_blink.png\u0022 title=\u0022:blink:\u0022\u003E (*nerd moment), a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.0 is when the rocket\u0027s thrust is equal to its weight, determined by the planet\u0027s gravity. At a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1, the ratio is balanced and therefore the rocket theoretically never moves.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDisclaimer: This nerd speech does not include the fact that as fuel drains, the weight of the craft decreases, and the ratio climbs over 1.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Csub\u003EAdvice each sold separately\u003C/sub\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Csub\u003EFor well qualified buyers only\u003C/sub\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-23T22:39:56Z\u0022 title=\u002204/23/2023 10:39  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by DerkyJerkyWreaksHavoc\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cashdesigner","CreatedById":228717,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-29T17:55:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224276273\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221682283013\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/23/2023 at 3:50 PM, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPerhaps a revision of \u0022a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.01 to the Mun and Back\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah that would probobly be more doable\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DennisB","CreatedById":227553,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-30T06:23:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn theory it\u0027s possible to start from Kerbin and Mun and to land on Kerbin, but I don\u0027t know how to land on Mun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Landing on Kerbin is obviously possible with aerobraking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Launch from Kerbin should be also possible. You can start horizontal with a plane, compensating the gravity with aerodynamic lift.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Launch from Mun would be much more difficult, because of the absence of an atmosphere. You would have to start horizontal again, and reach orbital speed, driving on the surface, or a little less, if you have a slope, which you can use as a ramp.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I have no idea, how to land on Mun, because you have to do it, with nearly orbital speed (with unbreakable parts?). And I also don\u0027t know, how you could adjust the throttle, keeping \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E=1 all the time (is there a mod for it?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have no intentions to participate in the challenge, and I don\u0027t have KSP2. I made just some thoughts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Probably it should be \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u0026lt;=1, because with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E=1 all the time, you will run out of fuel before you reach Mun.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-04-30T06:43:30Z\u0022 title=\u002204/30/2023 06:43  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EApril 30, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by DennisB\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"QF9E","CreatedById":201203,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-04-30T07:26:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224278256\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221682835814\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227553\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DennisB\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n59 minutes ago, DennisB said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I have no idea, how to land on Mun, because you have to do it, with nearly orbital speed (with unbreakable parts?).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo be fair the challenge does not say in so many words that you have to land on the Mun, only that you have to make a trip to the Mun. It seems to me that a free return trajectory around the Mun would suffice.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-09T09:51:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224291579\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022216724\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221686289606\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229335\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022David james\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, David james said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAchieving a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E of 1.0 in Kerbal Space Program is challenging and might not be possible. The stock game lacks a \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Thrust-to-weight ratio\u0022\u003ETWR\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E display, requiring mods like Micro-Engineer. It would involve constant throttle adjustments and could waste a lot of fuel. Good luck with your attempt, but it\u0027s a tough challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t forget the fact it\u0027s physically impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}